## Working convention: Interpretable Context (mini-MWP)

This repo follows my mini-MWP methodology — a personal adaptation of the [Model Workspace Protocol](https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.16021). In short: filesystem-structured stages, markdown-as-context, single agent with human review between stages, and PR-per-worktree as the handoff mechanism. See `~/mini-mwp/methodology/` for the full writeup.

---

## Workflow rule: always PR into `main`, via a worktree

**Never commit directly to `main`.** Use:

```bash
git worktree add ../{{repoSlug}}-wt-<short-slug> -b <branch-name> main
```

Then `cd` into the worktree, work there, push, open PR. After merge: `git worktree remove ../{{repoSlug}}-wt-<short-slug>` + `git branch -d <branch>`.

Default behavior even for one-line fixes. Only skip if I explicitly say so.

